      "body" : "Note: The command line for launching bitcoind should not have RPC commands such as getinfo included, those should be issued by a second instance of bitcoind to issue rpcconnect commands. e.g.:\r\nconsole 1: bitcoind -datadir=/home/foo/bar\r\nconsole 2 (after bitcoind has started): bitcoind getinfo\r\n\r\nBehavior with Bitcoin 0.7.0 PPA on Kubuntu 12.04 (with no extra \"getinfo\"; can't test with \"getinfo\" right now) and Bitcoin 0.7.1 on Win7 x64 (with or without extra \"getinfo\"): no crash, just the directory does not exist error.",
